<% content_for :title do %> - SDK - Widget design and style guide<% end %>
<div id="widgetdesignandstyle" class="widgetsdk_container">
    <h1>Widget design and style guide</h1>
    <p>This guide will help you style your widgets allowing them to fit seemlessle into the Sakai OAE suite of Widgets maintain a high standard for content presentation, and to maintain a high level of user experience across the system.</p>

    <div class="wl-widget-item first">
        <%= image_tag "developer_typehierarchy_icon.png", :alt => "Type hierarchy", :class => "descriptive_icon" %>
        <div class="descriptive_text">
            <h2>Type hierarchy</h2>
            <p>All typographic sizes for headers and body copy.</p>
            <%= link_to "View", "/sdk/widgetdesignandstyle/typography", :class => "wl-link-button wl-button wl-header-button blue"%>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wl-widget-item">
        <%= image_tag "developer_colorpalette_icon.png", :alt => "Color palette", :class => "descriptive_icon" %>
        <div class="descriptive_text">
            <h2>Color palette</h2>
            <p>The main colours used within Sakai OAE for all aspects of the interface, from the hover states of lists to the colours used in the system messages.</p>
            <%= link_to "View", "/sdk/widgetdesignandstyle/colorpalette", :class => "wl-link-button wl-button wl-header-button blue"%>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wl-widget-item">
        <%= image_tag "developer_template_icon.png", :alt => "Template and image sizes", :class => "descriptive_icon" %>
        <div class="descriptive_text">
            <h2>Template and image sizes</h2>
            <p>Widths of columns within each template, allowing the created modules to fit seamlessly into the system.</p>
            <%= link_to "View", "/sdk/widgetdesignandstyle/widgetexamples01", :class => "wl-link-button wl-button wl-header-button blue"%>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wl-widget-item">
        <%= image_tag "developer_navbuttonlinkusage_icon.png", :alt => "Navigation, Button usage and link language", :class => "descriptive_icon" %>
        <div class="descriptive_text">
            <h2>Navigation, Button usage and Link language</h2>
            <p>All states of navigational items, be they primary, secondary or tertiatry for use within the page widgets, headers, and overlays.</p>
            <%= link_to "View", "/sdk/widgetdesignandstyle/navigationalitems", :class => "wl-link-button wl-button wl-header-button blue"%>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wl-widget-item">
        <%= image_tag "developer_speechbubble_icon.png", :alt => "Iconography", :class => "descriptive_icon" %>
        <div class="descriptive_text">
            <h2>iconography</h2>
            <p>The generic style of icons has to ahear to a few basic rules. The examples here will show you ho to creat your own icons to gel with the Sakai OAE icon family.</p>
            <%= link_to "View", "/sdk/widgetdesignandstyle/iconography", :class => "wl-link-button wl-button wl-header-button blue"%>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wl-widget-item">
        <%= image_tag "developer_interaction_icon.png", :alt => "Interaction models", :class => "descriptive_icon" %>
        <div class="descriptive_text">
            <h2>Interaction models</h2>
            <p>Forms and  validation, dropdowns, expandable panels, widget settings</p>
            <%= link_to "View", "/sdk/widgetdesignandstyle/interactionmodels", :class => "wl-link-button wl-button wl-header-button blue"%>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr class="wl-push wl-hidden"/>
</div>